<TEXT>
a convict serving a life sentence for drug 
smuggling and the helicopter pilot who tried to spring him from 
prison but crashed were charged tuesday with conspiracy and 
attempted escape 
ben kramer a nationally known powerboat racer serving a life 
sentence for marijuana smuggling and seaurchin diver charlie 
stevens both 34 were charged tuesday afternoon as they 
recuperated at jackson memorial hospital 
stevens crashed monday as his twoseater bell helicopter snagged 
on a 14foot wire security fence around the metropolitan 
correctional center during an attempt to take kramer out of a 
recreation yard 
kramer suffered a compound fracture to his left ankle and was 
listed in satisfactory condition 
stevens with two broken legs and injuries to the head neck and 
back was in good condition 
a court appearance has not been scheduled yet 
stevens started to take off from the compound with kramer 
hanging to the helicopter skids attempting to enter the cockpit 
marshal thomas figmik wrote in the arrest affidavit the 
helicopters blades became entangled in a security fence and the 
helicopter crashed 
authorities say stevens who most recently lived on the oregan 
coast was an amateur pilot just learning to fly helicopters in 
december he paid 35000 in cash for the chopper from a california 
flight instructor and got four hours of flying instruction 
