a high school principal has pulled a story from 
the school newspaper about the senior class valedictorian a 
straighta honors student who is pregnant with her second child 
chester smith principal of jack yates high school vetoed an 
article by a student reporter about carrie mae dixon who is five 
months pregnant and carries a full load of classes including 
physics calculus and economics 
the story titled against all odds student becomes 
valedictorian despite motherhood details miss dixons first 
pregnancy how she was shuffled among relatives after her mother 
died and her stepfather deserted her and eight siblings and her 
dream of a middleclass home and a middleclass life 
miss dixon who spends two to five hours a night with her books 
has no one to babysit her 18monthold daughter terrisha 
keandrea she keeps the child occupied with paper and a pencil and 
she writes while i write 
miss dixon 17 has been accepted to the university of houston 
and has two scholarships she plans to major in chemical 
engineering 
a school reporter first tried to do a story about miss dixon 
last year after she was spotted on a cold rainy day standing at a 
bus stop holding an umbrella over her daughter while studying a 
math text a school official blocked the story 
according to newspaper editor shuronda robinson smith rejected 
the story thursday when she submitted the newspaper for approval 
smith told reporters tuesday that he thought the article was too 
personal to be printed in the newspaper and houston independent 
school district superintendent joan raymond agreed 
in his judgment the article was too highly personal 
sensitive to the young lady and he did not permit it to be 
