france for the first time has sent arms 
to guerrillas fighting vietnams occupation of cambodia newspapers 
today quoted a senior thai officer as saying 
the shipments are going to the forces of prince norodom 
sihanouk president of the threeparty guerrilla coalition said 
gen sunthorn kongsompong the armed forces chief of staff 
the latest shipment arrived a few days ago sunthorn was quoted 
as saying tuesday according to the bangkok post thai rath and 
other newspapers the arms are being shipped through thai territory 
to the guerrillas on the thaicambodian border the newspapers said 
the reports said sunthorn dismissed concerns the aid may affect 
vietnams plan to and withdraw all its troops from cambodia by 
sept 30 ending a 10year military occupation vietnam has 
demanded a simultanous halt in outside military aid to the 
guerrillas 
sunthorn said the soviet union vietnams main source of foreign 
aid will continue to pressure hanoi for a pullout 
the resistance receives the bulk of its weapons from china 
the strongest cambodian resistance group the khmer rouge 
seized power in cambodia in 1975 and over the next four years 
killed hundreds of thousands of people as they tried to create a 
primitive agrarian society 
vietnam invaded in december 1978 and ousted the khmer rouge 
france has been a strong diplomatic supporter of the resistance 
and has played host to talks between sihanouk and hun sen the 
prime minister of the vietnameseinstalled government in cambodia 
the french made cambodia a protectorate in 1864 and granted 
independence in 1953 with sihanouk as its leader 
