a united airlines boeing 747 en 
route to sydney australia turned back to auckland today when an 
engine overheated soon after takeoff the airline said 
the plane landed normally with one of its four engines shut 
down said wayne dodge uniteds manager for new zealand 
he said the pilot shut down the engine down when he realized it 
was overheating the plane was carrying 173 passenger and 18 crew 
members 
the passengers were transferred to an air new zealand flight 
which left soon after 
it was a nonemergency the pilot didnt have to dump fuel 
michael merlini uniteds manager for australia told the 
associated press 
united has had a rash of problems in recent weeks in february 
a cargo door blew out on a jumbo flying the 811 route from honolulu 
to auckland sweeping nine people to their deaths 
late last month a united 747 turned back to auckland 45 minutes 
after takeoff when an engine failed and earlier this month a jumbo 
damaged its undercarriage during a heavy landing at sydney on the 
flight from auckland 
