lands complain of feeling like stone fodder thrown into a 
futile battle with palestinians and say settler and army brutality 
have corrupted israels morals 
i am reaching the end of my thoughts about zionism in this 
country my next war will be against jews thats what i feel 
said one officer uri dan 
his comments and those of 10 other reserve officers appear in 
commanders reflections a 34page booklet published by the 
kibbutz artzi movement that unites 85 of israels 160odd 
kibbutzim or communal farms 
the booklet released on tuesday quotes remarks made by the 
officers members of kibbutzim in a february conversation with 
maj gen amram mitzna head of the armys central command their 
ranks were not given 
the officers single out army regulations on opening fire lack 
of proper ammunition pressure of increased reserve duty and their 
feeling of futility in dealing with the palestinian revolt 
the 16month uprising known to arabs as the intefadeh in 
the occupied west bank and the gaza strip has claimed at least 439 
palestinian and 18 israeli lives 
once in four five months you are called to intefadeh and you 
see that nothing has changed maybe it only got worse i can even 
say that in a certain way you feel like stone fodder said 
omri frish of the kibbutz mesilot 
