<TEXT>
attackers ambushed the first un convoy 
bringing relief supplies to rebelheld southern sudan destroying 
the lead vehicle and reportedly killing eight rebel escorts un 
officials said today 
diane weathers a un world food program spokeswoman said a 
driver and two assistants also were wounded in the tuesday 
afternoon attack 14 miles west of the sudan peoples liberation 
army base at kapoeta 
the 14truck convoy was carrying 100 tons of food and relief 
supplies to the town of torit 100 miles west of kapoeta 
it was the first relief convoy to torit under operation 
lifelinesudan the unorganized effort to stock more than 
100000 tons of food and supplies in southern sudan before rain in 
may makes transportation virtually impossible 
the effort is intended to avert another tragedy like that in 
1988 when relief officials say about 500000 people died from 
drought 
the operation began april 1 after the government and the rebels 
agreed to allow aid to move unhampered through rebelheld and 
governmentcontrolled land 
un officials in nairobi did not say who they believed was 
responsible for tuesdays ambush but they said it was unlikely 
sudan peoples liberation army rebels would attack their own 
members 
the sudan peoples liberation army took up arms against the 
moslemdominated government in 1983 demanding greater autonomy and 
economic development for the predominantly christian and animist 
south 
a french monitor for the world food program was riding with the 
convoy when it was attacked and reported the incident tuesday night 
to un officials said ms weathers 
eight rebel escorts members of the peoples liberation armys 
sudan relief and rehabilitation association were killed by 
automatic weapon fire and the lead vehicle was destroyed by some 
sort of missile said paul mitchell a un spokesman mitchell 
did not know whether the rebel escorts were armed 
he said that because of the attack operation lifelines 
overland route to torit from kapoeta would be suspended he said an 
airlift from the ugandan city of entebbe would begin friday to 
torit which was captured by rebels in march 
ms weathers said in the last three weeks torits population 
has soared from 3000 to 25000 as displaced sudanese seeking 
shelter and food pour in she said the un expected the population 
to grow to as many as 50000 
ms weathers said that while tuesdays attack interrupted the 
overland relief operation to torit the remainder of the aid 
operation would continue 
the united nations planned to move 25000 tons of food and 
supplies before rains begin in midmay but to date un convoys 
have moved only 120 tons of food to kapoeta from kenya said ms 
weathers 
the norwegian peoples aid in conjunction with the 
californiabased world vision relief agency and the us agency for 
international development has trucked several thousand tons of 
relief supplies to kapoeta since october in another relief 
operation 
from uganda a joint world food programcatholic relief services 
airlift has carried 3000 tons of relief supplies to the city of 
juba home to an estimated 300000 war refugees and residents 
