thousands of students demanding the 
overthrow of president roh taewoo battled riot police today with 
firebombs and rocks in at least 10 cities and protesters attacked 
a us military base in seoul 
police firing tear gas battled students in campus and street 
clashes marking the anniversary of the april 19 1960 student 
revolt that toppled the syngman rhee government violent protests 
were reported in seoul kwangju chonju chungju pusan taejon 
wonju kangnung chunchon and iri 
execute roh taewoo and yankee go home students 
screamed as they beat drums and brass gongs 
yonhap the south korean news agency said about 37000 students 
took part in protests at 112 colleges nationwide but it did not 
say how many were violent police said they had no overall figures 
on the protests 
several police officers and students were injured but police 
officials in seoul said they had no details on injuries or arrests 
the protests appeared to be the most serious in recent months 
a band of protesters hurled about 20 firebombs into the us 
armys camp isabell in seoul during the night but caused only minor 
damage police and us military officials said the protesters 
fled before they could be caught 
radical students claim the united states helps keep the roh 
government in power and are demanding withdrawal of the 43000 us 
troops based in the nation students have staged a series of 
attacks on us facilities in recent months 
more than 1000 students at hankook university in seoul staged a 
furious battle pelting police with hundreds of firebombs and 
rocks police in fatigues and visored helmets fired scores of tear 
gas canisters and made several charges to force the protesters back 
similar clashes occurred at at least 12 other seoul colleges 
after police blocked students from marching into the streets 
but a student call for evening protests in the center of seoul 
was mostly ignored with just a few protesters yelling slogans on 
sidewalks before being quickly swept away by thousands of riot 
police 
student leaders urged students to imitate the example of the 
1960 revolt 
we must strike down the roh dictatorship and establish true 
democracy in korea a leader at hankook said as students cheered 
the government put riot police on top alert nationwide to block 
protests at least 20000 riot police were deployed in seoul riot 
units guarded key government buildings and some major intersections 
police officials also said security was increased near 
government buildings and embassies 
the radicals frequently stage violent demonstrations and attack 
government offices they lack popular support because of their 
extreme views and they are not seen as a serious threat to the roh 
government 
the radical students who represent a small but powerful 
minority on college campuses are trying to form an antigovernment 
alliance with militant trade union groups campaigning for major 
wage increases and other concessions 
about 1000 striking electronic workers clashed today with riot 
police in the southeastern city of changwon after a protest march 
a major crackdown was launched on labor strikes after roh warned 
last week that strikes threatened to hamstring the economy roh 
said strikes had cost 24 billion in lost production and reduced 
exports by 600 million this year 
roh a former general won presidential elections in december 
1987 and has helped introduce broad democratic reforms but many 
koreans still identify his government with his authoritarian 
predecessor chun doohwan 
