derailment of a highspeed passenger train in which 12 cars jumped 
the rails and tumbled down a rocky embankment officials said 
another 137 people were injured 
twelve cars on the new delhibound express derailed tuesday 280 
miles south of the capital near lalitpur while the train was 
traveling at up to 70 mph said mathew john the chief of railway 
safety 
john said the two dieselpowered engines first eight cars and 
the guards car on the karnataka express remained upright on the 
rails authorities said the train began its journey monday from 
bangalore 820 miles south of the accident site and was running 
several hours late 
press trust of india quoting survivors said the cars 
overturned when the speeding train braked sharply near a bridge 
about 1000 people were on board the train 
the train was at a very high speed when i suddenly heard 
wheels screeching then there was a series of thuds and we found 
our coach overturning passenger vn murthy was quoted as 
telling the news agency 
murthy 36 said a child was heading toward the restroom when 
the train derailed she just got crushed murthy told the news 
agency 
about 20 victims were killed instantly and the rest died shortly 
after arrival at lalitpur civil hospital two miles from the 
accident site john said he said 137 people were seriously injured 
the dead included four men from a 14member karnataka 
kabaddi team the team was traveling to haridwar in north india 
to participate in a tournament for the sport a sort of 
roughandtumble version of tag 
john said an inquiry into the cause of the derailment will begin 
friday 
