now expects to provide less than half the 100000 tons of relief 
goods believed to be necessary if a second consecutive summer 
disaster is to be avoided 
when the relief effort began april 1 the united nations planned 
to stockpile supplies at strategic points in southern and 
southwestern sudan for people escaping famine caused by the 
6yearlong civil war in the region 
