committee on aging to elaborate on a study that has found the 
medicare program paid at least 500 million in 1987 for hospital 
admissions that were related to an adverse prescription drug 
reaction or an overdose 
he told the panel that is a conservative figure because 
hospitals do not always flag drug reaction cases in the records 
they submit for medicare reimbursements 
preliminary results from the report released previously found 
that the elderly account for 200000 or 39 percent of all 
hospitalizations from drug reactions and half of deaths from such 
reactions 
