<DOCNO> AP890419-0203 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
about 2000 americans are hospitalized 
annually with a split wall in the bodys major artery an ailment 
that sent lucille ball into emergency heart surgery a heart 
specialist said wednesday 
its one of the most severely painful diseases a human has to 
suffer although not everyone who gets an aortic dissection 
experiences extreme pain said dr thomas robertson chief of 
cardiac diseases at the national heart lung and blood institute in 
bethesda md 
the condition also called a dissecting aortic aneurysm 
involves a tear that splits the wall of the aorta the main artery 
connecting the heart to smaller arteries that carry blood 
throughout the body 
although 2000 americans reach hospitals and are diagnosed with 
a split aorta each year an unknown number of others suffer the 
ailment and have it misdiagnosed as a heart attack or die before 
they arrive at an emergency room robertson said during a telephone 
interview 
he estimated aortic dissection kills about half of those it 
afflicts often when the split aorta wall ruptures to cause 
internal hemorrhaging 
of those who reach hospitals and undergo surgery about 
threefourths survive hospitalization death is most likely during 
the operation itself he added 
the aorta emerges from the left ventricle the hearts main 
pumping chamber passes upward and arches over the top of the 
heart then passes down behind the heart and into the abdomen 
during aortic dissection a tear suddenly develops in the tissue 
that makes up the wall of the aorta the layers of tissue separate 
allowing blood to flow into the gap which then painfully expands 
like a balloon the pressure can make the tear spread up or down a 
greater length of the artery 
an aortic dissection is different than the much more common and 
conventional aortic aneurysm in which the artery wall is weakened 
and balloons outward but layers of the artery wall dont split 
in miss balls condition the beginning portion of her aorta 
near the heart began to tear apart and that tearing progressed 
all the way down into her abdomen her surgeon dr robert kass 
said tuesday night 
the split wall involved essentially her whole aorta he 
added 
during the sixhour operation at cedarssinai medical center 
kass said he removed the 77yearold miss balls ascending aorta 
the short stretch of aorta that emerges from the ventricle and 
the aortic valve he replaced them with those taken from the 
cadaver of a 27yearold 
the aortic valve controls the flow of blood from the ventricle 
into the aorta kass said the expansion in miss balls split artery 
wall unroofed the aortic valve to make it leak a leaky valve 
can cause heart failure because blood cant be pumped out of the 
heart efficiently 
during a news conference kass didnt explain why the rest of 
the aorta wasnt replaced 
but robertson said many arteries branch off the aorta so its 
safest to replace only the part where the tear started 
a surgeon can tack together the place where the split wall 
continues preventing ballooning by blocking blood from flowing 
into the gap he said 
kass also said he detached the ends of miss balls coronary 
arteries where they connected to her ascending aorta then 
reattached them to the newly implanted aorta restoring blood flow 
that nourishes the heart 
sometimes an aorta with a split wall isnt replaced but is 
repaired with synthetic materials such as by inserting a knitted 
dacron tube inside the defective section of aorta 
doctors dont know why aortic walls sometimes split hardening 
of the arteries and congenital artery weakness have been suspected 
but the risk is increased by high blood pressure which kass said 
miss ball has suffered for several years 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

