the demand let my people go originally was flung by the 
ancient jewish leader moses at the egyptian pharaoh in the worlds 
earliest struggle for religious freedom nearly 4000 years ago 
those words still are relevant says gerald strober 
information officer of the ncsj pharaoh has begun to loosen up 
and we welcome it but we must remain ever vigilant 
