<TEXT>
the average age of planes in the fleet of 
turboprop aircraft used by airlines in north america is 31 years 
younger than the average for the jetliner fleet says an aviation 
consulting firm 
the average age of turboprop aircraft used by airlines in the 
united states and canada is 93 years while the average age of jet 
aircraft is 124 years according to a study released tuesday by 
avmark inc which appraises aircraft throughout the world 
the report prepared for the regional airline associations 
international conference on aging commuter aircraft in kansas city 
mo next week says the average age for the worldwide fleet of 
turboprops is 11 years old compared with more than 13 years for 
passenger jets 
the study which groups aircraft by regions of the world says 
the north american turboprop fleet is the youngest while the 
middle east has the oldest aircraft with an average age of 154 
years turboprops in asia and australia average 135 years in 
latin america 13 years in africa 124 years and in europe 121 
years according to the report 
the average age of the commuterregional turboprop fleet is 
expected to experience a decline as the operators continue to 
expand their operations through acquisition of a substantial number 
of new aircraft in the next decade the report says 
it says 681 percent of the turboprops in north america were 
built within the last nine years while 76 percent were built 20 
or more years ago the oldest turboprops are those that carry 40 to 
50 passengers while the youngest are in the 2039 passenger 
category 
the youngest fleets according to avmark belong to the midway 
express system 34 years and piedmont commuter 38 years while 
the oldest are operated by air canada connector 132 years and 
aloha island 127 years 
other fleets in the report and the average age of their 
turboprop planes are delta connection 56 american eagle 57 
northwest airlink 65 united express 66 eastern express 71 
twexpress 79 allegheny commuter 81 alaska commuter 90 pan 
am express 10 continental express 108 and canadian partner 11 
the report covers airplanes in use as of july 1988 and covers 
