<TEXT>
wells fargo bank announced wednesday it 
will expand the international services available to its customers 
through an agreement with hongkong and shanghai banking corp 
at the same time the san franciscobased banking concern will 
dispose of its four remaining overseas offices in seoul korea 
singapore hong kong and tokyo 
in an effort to concentrate on its core market in california 
wells fargo has been reducing its direct involvement in overseas 
activity except for the area of trade financing 
hongkongbank will serve wells fargo customers outside the united 
states and will take over its business and office in hong kong it 
also will help dispose of wells fargos tokyo office the company 
said 
the los angeles and san francisco offices of hongkongbank will 
also refer their retail banking business to wells fargo however 
the offices will retain their corporate customers in california 
wells fargo chairman carl e reichardt termed the agreement with 
hongkongbank the first of its kind for a major us bank and a 
forerunner of how global banking will be done in the 1990s 
</TEXT>
